CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 6, 1957, pg. 9 reads: "$500 Fire - Fire in this two-story brick dwelling at 37 Manilla St., Saturday, caused $300 damages to the building and $200 to the contestants, as estimated by firemen. Willie Clay is the occupant. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Fire fighter standing behind fire truck parked in front of two-story brick row house, 37 Manilla Street
